    "As concerns educational attainment, eight of the study participants in the experimental group had a master's degree, while 14 had a bachelor's degree, and three were bachelor's students at the time when the study was conducted.",
    "In the control group, which consisted of 21 participants, all except one were students, with the remaining participant being a faculty member.",
    "Regarding age, eight respondents were 18-24, while 13 were 25-35 years old.",
    "Furthermore, most of the participants (N = 12) were male, while eight were female, and one indicated \"other\" as gender.",
    "Finally, regarding educational attainment, six respondents were bachelor's students, 12 had a bachelor's degree, and three held a master's degree."
